olive oil
2 potato
1 Cucumber
1 sprig spring onion
½ bunch Baby Broccoli
1 packet Asian Greens
3 clove Garlic
1 packet Pork Loin Steaks
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet oyster sauce
2 packet sweet chilli sauce
6 bao buns
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Season with
salt, drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, slice cucumber into sticks.
• Thinly slice spring onion.
• Halve any thicker stalks of baby broccoli
(see ingredients) lengthways.
• Roughly chop Asian greens.
• Finely chop garlic.
• Slice pork loin steaks into 1cm strips.
• In a medium bowl, combine pork, sweet soy
seasoning, half the garlic and a drizzle of
olive oil.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook baby broccoli,
tossing, until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and remaining garlic and
cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add oyster sauce
and toss to combine. Transfer to a serving plate
and cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot,
cook pork in batches, tossing, until golden,
2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then return all pork to
the pan and add sweet chilli sauce, tossing
to coat.

• Place bao buns on a microwave-safe plate and
cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave on high for 1 minute. Set aside to rest
for 1 minute.

• Gently halve bao buns and spread with
mayonnaise. Fill with sticky sweet chilli pork,
cucumber and spring onion.
• Serve with potato fries and oyster sauce
greens. Enjoy!